.TH MANUALTOOLCHANGE "9" "2026-06-05" "LinuxCNC Documentation" "HAL Component"
.SH NAME

manualtoolchange \- Manual tool change with REST API for UI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.HP
.B load manualtoolchange [manualtoolchange.\fIN\fB]
.SH DESCRIPTION


Provides HAL pins for iocontrol tool-change handshaking and a REST API
for a remote UI (manualtoolchange_ui.py).  Replaces the old
hal_manualtoolchange userspace Python component.

HAL pins (directly wired to iocontrol):
  - change (bit, in): tool change requested by iocontrol
  - number (s32, in): requested tool number
  - change_button (bit, in): external button to confirm change
  - changed (bit, out): tool change confirmed

REST API (via GMI):
  - GET  /state   \[u2014] returns {change, number, changed}
  - POST /confirm \[u2014] sets changed=true

The UI polls GET /state, shows a dialog when change goes true,
and calls POST /confirm when the operator clicks Continue.
The change_button pin allows confirming without the UI (e.g. a
physical button wired through HAL).

